cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper is about scene graph generation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new architecture for semantic extraction, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with language processing to some extent, as it involves predicting relations between entities, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category. Finally, the paper uses the Visual Genome dataset, which is a dataset of images and their annotations, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
